Description: Tillitis TKey-based LUKS disk encryption unlock
 TKey-LUKS provides hardware-based LUKS disk encryption unlock using the
 Tillitis TKey security device. It implements a secure three-factor
 authentication system combining:
  - Something you have: Physical TKey device (contains UDS hardware secret)
  - Something you know: Password (used twice: USS derivation + BLAKE2b)
  - System-unique: Machine identity (machine-id salt)
 .
 Key features (v1.1.1):
  - Improved USS derivation using PBKDF2 (no USS files on disk)
  - Consistent salt availability across setup and boot
  - Cryptographic boot-time unlock via initramfs hooks
  - Touch-to-unlock physical authentication
  - Multi-layer key derivation (USS → CDI → BLAKE2b)
  - Compatible with LUKS1 and LUKS2
  - Comprehensive security documentation and troubleshooting
 .
 This package includes:
  - tkey-luks-client: Client application for key derivation
  - TKey device application: Firmware for hardware key operations
  - Initramfs hooks: Boot-time integration scripts with salt management
